    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Assuming Unnecessary Burdens</strong>&mdash;Many mothers spend their time in doing needless nothings. They give <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"250\"></span> their whole attention to the things of time and sense, and do not pause to think of the things of eternal interest. How many neglect their children, and the little ones grow up coarse, rough, and uncultivated!<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">4<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"ST 7-22-1889\" data-link=\"820.9524\">The Signs of the Times, July 22, 1889</span>.</span></a></sup>",
