    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "If woman looks to God for strength and comfort and in His fear seeks to perform her daily duties, she will win the respect and confidence of her husband and see her children coming to maturity honorable men and women, having moral stamina to do right. But mothers who neglect present opportunities, and let their duties and burdens fall upon others, will find that their responsibility remains the same, and they will reap in bitterness what they have sown in carelessness and neglect. There is no chance work in this life; the harvest will be determined by the character of the seed sown.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">6<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"nol-ink\" title=\"ST 4-4-1911\">The Signs of the Times, April 4, 1911</span> (<span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"ST 9-9-1886.8\" data-link=\"820.7470\">The Signs of the Times, September 9, 1886</span>).</span></a></sup>",
